HEADWORD: Marseilles
<hw>Mar*seilles"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A general term
for certain kinds of fabrics, which are formed of two series of threads
interlacing each other, thus forming double cloth, quilted in the loom;
-- so named because first made in <city>Marseilles</city>,
France.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marsh</ent>⟦br⟧
